{
  "text": "Corneal rigidity is permanently reduced after both LASIK and PRK treatments, [CITATION_1] reducing the biomechanical stability of the cornea. Some restiffening may occur in the PRK group in 18 using a mathematical model to estimate the relative differences in postoperative stromal tensile strength after PRK, LASIK, and SMILE, report that after removal of 100 \u00b5m of corneal stroma, the total stromal tensile strength would be 68% for PRK and 54% for LASIK.",
